00:13:07.820 --> 00:13:11.000
in practicing different
optical setups, that

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:12.740
is called a grating.

00:13:12.740 --> 00:13:15.410
So grating-- you can think of
it as a material, in this case,

00:13:15.410 --> 00:13:16.700
that--

00:13:16.700 --> 00:13:19.130
the one that I'm going to show
is called a phase grating.

00:13:19.130 --> 00:13:22.520
Basically, the index or
refraction within the material

00:13:22.520 --> 00:13:26.470
varies in a given way-- in
this case, sinusoidally.

00:13:26.470 --> 00:13:29.500
So it's a periodic variation
of the index of refraction,

00:13:29.500 --> 00:13:33.790
and then when the light
