00:18:33.890 --> 00:18:37.820
what Pepe showed in real life.

00:18:37.820 --> 00:18:41.340
So a grating basically,
as Pepe mentioned,

00:18:41.340 --> 00:18:45.260
is a periodic,
thin transparency.

00:18:45.260 --> 00:18:47.390
So we've talked about thin
transparencies before.

00:18:47.390 --> 00:18:50.360
We mentioned that they
modulate in general.

00:18:50.360 --> 00:18:52.840
Thin transparencies
modulate the amplitude

00:18:52.840 --> 00:18:56.840
and the phase of the
optical field, so

00:18:56.840 --> 00:18:59.690
in that particular case,
when the thin transparency's

00:18:59.690 --> 00:19:03.950
a periodic function of space,
then we'll call it a grating.

00:19:03.950 --> 00:19:08.930
And I guess for clarity
of presentation,

00:19:08.930 --> 00:19:13.970
it is customary to classify
gratings as amplitude or phase,

00:19:13.970 --> 00:19:17.120
depending on whether
the grating acts

00:19:17.120 --> 00:19:21.740
upon the magnitude of
the electromagnetic field

00:19:21.740 --> 00:19:24.650
or the phase of the
electromagnetic field.

00:19:24.650 --> 00:19:26.750
Now, this can cause a
little bit of confusion

00:19:26.750 --> 00:19:30.080
because we have
agreed to use the term

00:19:30.080 --> 00:19:34.610
amplitude to denote the complex
amplitude of the optical field.

00:19:34.610 --> 00:19:38.270
Confusingly enough, when people
talk about amplitude gratings,

00:19:38.270 --> 00:19:43.730
they should be calling
them magnitude gratings,

00:19:43.730 --> 00:19:47.060
because as you can see
in the case on the left,

00:19:47.060 --> 00:19:51.260
the transmission function
of an amplitude grating

00:19:51.260 --> 00:19:52.893
is a positive real number.

00:19:52.893 --> 00:19:54.310
So therefore, this
kind of grating

00:19:54.310 --> 00:19:59.990
acts directly onto the
magnitude of the optical field.

00:19:59.990 --> 00:20:03.530
Nevertheless, for
historical reasons,

00:20:03.530 --> 00:20:05.030
people call these are gratings--

00:20:05.030 --> 00:20:08.690
I suppose they call
them magnitude--

00:20:08.690 --> 00:20:10.880
I'm sorry, they call
them amplitude gratings.

00:20:10.880 --> 00:20:13.700
So hopefully, this will
not create confusion.

00:20:13.700 --> 00:20:16.250
But anyway, the simplest
possible modulation

00:20:16.250 --> 00:20:18.890
is sinusoidal, and
you can see here

00:20:18.890 --> 00:20:22.190
sort of juxtaposed in
a sinusoidal amplitude

00:20:22.190 --> 00:20:25.760
grating and the
sinusoidal phase grating.

00:20:25.760 --> 00:20:28.940
So starting with the
amplitude grating,

00:20:28.940 --> 00:20:34.290
the complex transmission
function of the grating

00:20:34.290 --> 00:20:35.860
is actually not complex at all.

00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:39.210
It is a real positive
number, and what I've done

00:20:39.210 --> 00:20:42.460
is, on top of it, I've
plot its magnitude,

00:20:42.460 --> 00:20:44.760
which is, of course,
itself since this

00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:48.570
is a real positive
function, and its phase.

00:20:48.570 --> 00:20:51.900
And of course, the phase
is 0 because the phase

00:20:51.900 --> 00:20:53.640
of a complex number,
which happens

00:20:53.640 --> 00:20:58.260
to be real and positive, is 0.

00:20:58.260 --> 00:21:02.490
The quantities to mention here
are the period of the grating.

00:21:02.490 --> 00:21:07.470
We use the upper case
Greek symbol lambda, which

00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:12.150
looks like a hat, I guess.

00:21:12.150 --> 00:21:14.710
That symbol is called lambda.

00:21:14.710 --> 00:21:17.420
So this is the period of the
grating, so in this case,

00:21:17.420 --> 00:21:21.180
you can see the grating
seems to fulfill

00:21:21.180 --> 00:21:24.360
one undulation
between approximately

00:21:24.360 --> 00:21:27.660
minus 5 units and plus 5 units.

00:21:27.660 --> 00:21:31.460
Therefore, the period
here is 10 units.

00:21:31.460 --> 00:21:34.980
And actually, the unit I've
picked on the horizontal axis

00:21:34.980 --> 00:21:38.640
is the wavelength of the
light, so this grating

00:21:38.640 --> 00:21:41.700
has a period of 10 wavelengths.

00:21:41.700 --> 00:21:44.760
So if the light were a visible--

00:21:44.760 --> 00:21:48.390
green light has a wavelength
of approximately half

00:21:48.390 --> 00:21:53.760
a micrometer, so in real
units for the green light,

00:21:53.760 --> 00:21:58.530
the period here would have been
approximately 5 micrometers

00:21:58.530 --> 00:22:02.210
or 10 wavelengths.

00:22:02.210 --> 00:22:05.450
Then m-- we saw
the symbol m also

00:22:05.450 --> 00:22:07.670
when we talk about interference.

00:22:07.670 --> 00:22:14.520
We called m the contrast
between the brightest

00:22:14.520 --> 00:22:18.510
and the darkest part of a fringe
in the case of an interference

00:22:18.510 --> 00:22:19.440
pattern.

00:22:19.440 --> 00:22:21.420
In this case, we still
call it contrast,

00:22:21.420 --> 00:22:26.580
but it is between the
most transmissive part

00:22:26.580 --> 00:22:30.330
of the grating and the
darkest part of the grating.

00:22:30.330 --> 00:22:33.930
So this case, you can see that
it goes between approximately

00:22:33.930 --> 00:22:36.990
0.9 and 0.1.

00:22:36.990 --> 00:22:39.180
The maximum
transmissivity is 0.9,

00:22:39.180 --> 00:22:41.850
and the minimum
transmissivity is 0.1.

00:22:41.850 --> 00:22:45.570
So therefore, of the value of
m for the grating shown here

00:22:45.570 --> 00:22:48.420
is approximately 0.8.

00:22:48.420 --> 00:22:52.620
If the grating was swinging
between maximum 100%

00:22:52.620 --> 00:22:57.730
transmission, totally
bright and totally dark,

00:22:57.730 --> 00:22:59.100
that would have been 0.

00:22:59.100 --> 00:23:00.810
Then the contrast
would've been 1.

00:23:00.810 --> 00:23:05.380
So this is the function
of this m parameter here.

00:23:05.380 --> 00:23:08.670
And finally, we allow a phase
shift, which basically says,

00:23:08.670 --> 00:23:10.290
if the maximum--

00:23:10.290 --> 00:23:13.560
since the grating is written
as a cosine function here,

00:23:13.560 --> 00:23:18.030
phi tells me if the maximum
transmission, the maximum value

00:23:18.030 --> 00:23:21.930
of the cosine, is
centered with x equals 0

00:23:21.930 --> 00:23:23.380
on the horizontal axis--

00:23:23.380 --> 00:23:25.950
so you can see that, in this
case, it is indeed center.

00:23:25.950 --> 00:23:29.310
So therefore, the
phase phi would equal 0

00:23:29.310 --> 00:23:33.440
in the grating
shown in this case.

00:23:33.440 --> 00:23:35.970
So that's what I had
to say about that.

00:23:35.970 --> 00:23:38.830
Under the grating, I should
go to the phase grating.

00:23:38.830 --> 00:23:40.660
It is actually kind
of the opposite.

00:23:40.660 --> 00:23:42.490
So the phase
grating is expressed

00:23:42.490 --> 00:23:46.030
as a complex exponential
with a purely--

00:23:46.030 --> 00:23:52.790
with a pure phase without
any amplitude modulation.

00:23:52.790 --> 00:23:55.090
So it's magnitude then is 1.

00:23:55.090 --> 00:23:59.090
So you see that the
magnitude is a flat function,

00:23:59.090 --> 00:24:04.330
so this means that this grating
transmits all of the light.

00:24:04.330 --> 00:24:08.480
What it does do, though,
is it modulates the phase,

00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:10.450
and you can see that
it modulates the phase

00:24:10.450 --> 00:24:15.322
in a sinusoidal fashion.

00:24:15.322 --> 00:24:17.530
So this is what you see now
in the bottom plot, which

00:24:17.530 --> 00:24:20.260
is that the phase, the angle--

00:24:20.260 --> 00:24:22.390
by the way, the
phase, sometimes we

00:24:22.390 --> 00:24:28.850
denote the phase as this angular
symbol of a complex number.

00:24:28.850 --> 00:24:32.680
So the phase is simply the
argument of the exponent here,

00:24:32.680 --> 00:24:35.630
and is, itself, sinusoidal.

00:24:35.630 --> 00:24:39.320
And it also has a
period and a contrast.

00:24:39.320 --> 00:24:41.570
The contrast in this case
is called the phase contrast

00:24:41.570 --> 00:24:43.762
because we're talking
about the phase,

00:24:43.762 --> 00:24:45.220
and you can see
that, in this case,

00:24:45.220 --> 00:24:49.270
it is swinging also
approximately between plus 0.4

00:24:49.270 --> 00:24:50.590
and minus 0.4.

00:24:50.590 --> 00:24:54.280
So the contrast is
also 0.8 in this case,

00:24:54.280 --> 00:24:58.830
but it could be anything,
really, between minus pi and pi

00:24:58.830 --> 00:25:04.010
to get a complete
phase contrast.

00:25:04.010 --> 00:25:05.740
The other two
parameters are the same.

00:25:05.740 --> 00:25:08.740
The period is also
about 10 wavelengths,

00:25:08.740 --> 00:25:12.370
and the phase shift is 0.

00:25:12.370 --> 00:25:14.230
We have to be a little
bit careful here not

00:25:14.230 --> 00:25:19.250
to confuse the phase of the
grating with the phase shift.

00:25:19.250 --> 00:25:21.580
So again, the phase
shift is telling us

00:25:21.580 --> 00:25:27.040
whether that transmission
is aligned or no

00:25:27.040 --> 00:25:28.900
with the origin of
the coordinates.

00:25:28.900 --> 00:25:31.150
So this case,
since I have a sine

00:25:31.150 --> 00:25:32.650
in the phase of the
grating, you see

00:25:32.650 --> 00:25:36.190
that it assumes the
value 0 at x equals 0,

00:25:36.190 --> 00:25:38.200
so again, there's
no phase shift.

00:25:38.200 --> 00:25:42.100
So this phase shift is not to
be confused with the phase delay

00:25:42.100 --> 00:25:45.910
that the grating imposes
upon the complex amplitude

00:25:45.910 --> 00:25:47.480
of the electromagnetic field.

00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:48.920
So that's another
important point,

00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:52.080
and I would like
