00:27:37.030 --> 00:27:40.350
So the field will
propagate along the z-axis,

00:27:40.350 --> 00:27:44.970
and you can see that the light
that originally illuminated

00:27:44.970 --> 00:27:48.660
the grating actually now
splits into three parts.

00:27:48.660 --> 00:27:52.290
These are, also Pepe mentioned,
called diffraction orders.

00:27:52.290 --> 00:27:54.780
One of them propagates
straight through.

00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:57.630
That is called the
