01:09:38.319 --> 01:09:46.740
OK, so now, according to the
equation that we had before,

01:09:46.740 --> 01:09:50.880
if this is the x direction--
and let's ignore y for now.

01:09:50.880 --> 01:09:55.000
So basically, I can
neglect this term for now.

01:09:55.000 --> 01:10:03.170
And what we have is that the
sine factor will equal lambda

01:10:03.170 --> 01:10:05.710
upon the period.

01:10:05.710 --> 01:10:07.220
And it's bigger than 1.

01:10:07.220 --> 01:10:11.810
OK, mathematically, if
I have a complex angle,

01:10:11.810 --> 01:10:13.430
the sine can be bigger than 1.

01:10:13.430 --> 01:10:15.560
But what does this
physically mean?

01:10:15.560 --> 01:10:18.740
Physically, if you plug
into this equation here,

01:10:18.740 --> 01:10:27.440
you will get that the kz
squared equals 2 pi upon lambda

01:10:27.440 --> 01:10:37.430
squared minus 2 pi upon lambda
squared based on this equation.

01:10:37.430 --> 01:10:47.270
When I said that kx equals
2 pi upon lambda sine theta

01:10:47.270 --> 01:10:52.680
equals to pi upon lambda times
lambda over lambda equals 2 pi

01:10:52.680 --> 01:10:53.690
upon lambda--

01:10:53.690 --> 01:10:55.480
OK.

01:10:55.480 --> 01:11:01.490
So if I do that now, I will
get that the kz squared

01:11:01.490 --> 01:11:02.465
equals 2 pi.

01:11:11.640 --> 01:11:14.850
And the quantity inside the
square root is less than 0,

01:11:14.850 --> 01:11:20.670
so we'll get that the kz
now will equal plus minus.

01:11:20.670 --> 01:11:22.560
It will become imaginary.

01:11:22.560 --> 01:11:25.980
[INAUDIBLE] plus minus i
the square root of something

01:11:25.980 --> 01:11:26.882
positive.

01:11:31.975 --> 01:11:33.100
So what does this mean now?

01:11:33.100 --> 01:11:46.870
I have a wave whose amplitude
will be like e to the i kxx.

01:11:46.870 --> 01:11:48.820
Nothing changes here.

01:11:48.820 --> 01:11:56.220
But then it will be plus minus
i times something positive.

01:11:56.220 --> 01:12:04.432
Let's call this "alpha"
