subwavelength grating.

01:12:09.010 --> 01:12:17.090
So now, clearly here,
if you multiply the two

01:12:17.090 --> 01:12:20.100
imaginary units, we
will get a real number.

01:12:20.100 --> 01:12:24.180
So we get either exponential
decay or exponential explosion.

01:12:24.180 --> 01:12:27.380
Physically, you cannot expect
the wave to grow exponentially.

01:12:27.380 --> 01:12:30.470
That would mean someone
is supplying power,

01:12:30.470 --> 01:12:32.190
and there's nothing
like that here.

01:12:32.190 --> 01:12:33.590
So therefore, you
get a wave that

01:12:33.590 --> 01:12:38.440
will look like e to
the minus alpha z--

01:12:38.440 --> 01:12:40.240
there's a z here
in [INAUDIBLE]----

01:12:40.240 --> 01:12:44.180
times e to the minus
e to the plus ikxx.

01:12:44.180 --> 01:12:45.495
So what is this now?

01:12:45.495 --> 01:12:48.710
The e to the minus alpha
z's an exponential decay

01:12:48.710 --> 01:12:50.510
away from the grating.

01:12:50.510 --> 01:12:53.480
The e do the ikx is what
we call a "surface wave."

01:12:53.480 --> 01:12:55.470
It propagates like this.

01:12:55.470 --> 01:12:57.580
So actually, what you
get after this grating

01:12:57.580 --> 01:13:02.150
