01:13:06.730 --> 01:13:09.470
But anyway, as you get the
wave that propagates parallel

01:13:09.470 --> 01:13:12.710
to the grating, it is
called the "surface wave,"

01:13:12.710 --> 01:13:14.240
but it doesn't live very long.

01:13:14.240 --> 01:13:18.060
It decays exponentially
away from the grating.

01:13:18.060 --> 01:13:20.130
That is actually called
an "evanescent wave."

01:13:30.070 --> 01:13:31.710
